---
import PitchLayout from '@layouts/PitchLayout.astro';
---

<PitchLayout
  title="PC-12 Espresso Bar"
  description="A traveling espresso concept for the world's most remote runways."
>

  <!-- ======= 1. Title ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--title" id="slide-1">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="slide__overline reveal">Heist Studio</p>
      <h1 class="slide__heading slide__heading--large reveal">PC-12 Espresso Bar</h1>
      <p class="slide__subtitle reveal">A traveling espresso concept for the world's most remote runways</p>
      <p class="slide__mark fade-in">heist.studio</p>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-hint fade-in">
      <div class="scroll-hint__arrow"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 2. The Concept ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-2">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <h2 class="slide__heading">The Concept</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        A Pilatus PC-12 lands on a remote runway. The cargo door opens and a full espresso bar
        comes out&mdash;La Marzocco GS3, Mazzer grinder, beans roasted four days ago, everything
        packed in aluminum flight cases that unlatch like ordnance. The barista sets up on the
        lowered ramp. The pilot watches the road. Then whoever belongs to this landscape&mdash;cyclists,
        gauchos, shepherds&mdash;arrives under their own power, and espresso is served in the shadow
        of the wing.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        <strong>The concept is modular.</strong> Same plane, same bar. Different runway, different
        mountains, different guests.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 3. Three Acts ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-3">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Three Acts</h2>
      <div class="acts-grid stagger-children">
        <div class="act">
          <div class="act__number">I</div>
          <div class="act__title">Arrival &amp; Deploy</div>
          <p class="act__text">
            The PC-12 descends through a mountain valley. Landing. Shutdown. The cargo door opens.
            Flight cases unlatch. The bar assembles on the lowered ramp. Steam rises from the group
            head into thin air.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="act">
          <div class="act__number">II</div>
          <div class="act__title">Convergence</div>
          <p class="act__text">
            The locals arrive&mdash;by bike, by horse, on foot&mdash;from the landscape itself, not
            from the sky. Espresso passes from someone who flew here to someone who has always been
            here. The cup is the common language.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="act">
          <div class="act__number">III</div>
          <div class="act__title">Departure</div>
          <p class="act__text">
            Cases latch shut. The cargo door closes. The turboprop turns over. The locals leave the
            way they came. The runway empties. No evidence except the memory of something that
            shouldn't have existed here.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="acts-coda fade-in">The ritual is the main character. Both humans serve it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 4. The Setup ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-4">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <h2 class="slide__heading">The Setup</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        A real bush pilot flies the plane in. A real specialty coffee professional pulls the shots.
        2&ndash;3 shooter/producers behind camera&mdash;everyone shoots, everyone carries gear.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        <strong>Total on-site: 5&ndash;7 people.</strong> Small enough to fit in the aircraft.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The guests change by location but the rule doesn't: they arrive from the landscape, not from
        the sky. Cyclists who climbed to get here. Gauchos who rode in from an estancia. Shepherds
        who've been working this terrain since before the runway existed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 5. The Equipment ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-5">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <h2 class="slide__heading">The Equipment</h2>
      <ul class="equipment-list">
        <li><strong>La Marzocco GS3 MP</strong> &mdash; brushed stainless, dual boiler, paddle-actuated</li>
        <li><strong>Mazzer grinder</strong> &mdash; micro-adjusted for altitude</li>
        <li><strong>Aluminum flight cases</strong> &mdash; custom foam cutouts, latches like ordnance</li>
        <li><strong>Bar on the cargo ramp</strong> &mdash; assembles on the lowered door in minutes</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Late summer or early autumn. Snow on the peaks, strip clear. Cool enough that steam reads
        on camera.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 6. Switzerland ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--switzerland" id="slide-6">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Engadin Valley, Switzerland</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The highest paved airport in Europe, 5,600 feet up in a wide glacial valley. The Bernina
        massif fills the southern horizon. Morning light floods the valley floor while the peaks
        stay in shadow.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The PC-12 is built by Pilatus, twenty minutes north of here. Landing a Pilatus on a Swiss
        alpine runway with a full espresso bar in the hold is a homecoming story.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Road cyclists climbing an alpine pass</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Altitude, cold precision</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Pilatus brand homeland</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 7. Idaho ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--idaho" id="slide-7">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Frank Church Wilderness, Idaho</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Gravel strips cut into narrow valleys in the largest roadless area in the lower 48. You fly
        in or you don't come. Lodgepole pine and sage press in from both sides, and the Sawtooth
        Range forms the western wall.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Late August, the air smells like dust and resin. Fire-season haze drifts through the valleys
        and turns golden hour into something biblical.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Backcountry anglers or horse packers</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Remoteness, wilderness</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Self-reliance, Americana</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 8. Patagonia ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--patagonia" id="slide-8">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Torres del Paine, Patagonia</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Grass strips on estancia land. Nothing between you and the granite towers except steppe
        grass bending horizontal. The wind never stops. The barista braces against it&mdash;apron
        snapping sideways, hands steady on the portafilter while everything else moves.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The PC-12 with its high wing becomes the one windbreak on the runway.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Gauchos from a nearby estancia, arriving on horseback</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Wind, exposure</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Two kinds of working competence meeting over a cup</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 9. Iceland ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--iceland" id="slide-9">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Highland Interior, Iceland</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Packed gravel or volcanic cinder on plateaus between glaciers. Rhyolite hills, black sand,
        geothermal steam rising from fissures a hundred meters off the runway. No trees, no
        structures, no context for scale except the plane and the mountains.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The espresso is the only warm colour in the frame&mdash;amber crema against black basalt,
        moss green, sulfur yellow, cloud gray.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Shepherds doing the autumn r&eacute;ttir, on horseback with dogs</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Volcanic isolation, no shelter</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Ancient pastoral practice meets modern craft</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 10. Canadian Rockies ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--canada" id="slide-10">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">BC Interior, Canadian Rockies</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        The backcountry strips in BC sit at the base of valleys that make Idaho's look modest.
        Glaciers visible from the runway. The Columbia Icefield thirty minutes south by air.
        Everything here is about scale&mdash;the PC-12 is small against these mountains, and two
        people making espresso is smaller still.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        September. Larches turning gold against spruce and limestone. The air carries sound farther
        than it should.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Mountain guides or trail runners descending from a peak</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Scale, glacial cold</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">People who know this terrain encountering something foreign to it</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 11. Colorado ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--location slide--colorado" id="slide-11">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <p class="slide__overline">Location</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Leadville / Telluride, Colorado</h2>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Leadville sits at 9,934 feet&mdash;the highest airport in North America. At that altitude,
        water boils at 194&deg;F instead of 212&deg;F. Extraction changes. The GS3's pressure gauge
        reads the same but the physics are different.
      </p>
      <p class="slide__text">
        Telluride's strip sits in a box canyon with 13,000-foot peaks on three sides. Early October:
        aspen gold, first snow, crystalline alpine air.
      </p>
      <div class="location-meta">
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Guests</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Gravel cyclists on a high-altitude route</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">The adversary</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Thin air, altitude</div>
        </div>
        <div class="location-meta__item">
          <div class="location-meta__key">Pitch angle</div>
          <div class="location-meta__value">Physics as story</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 12. Deliverables ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-12">
    <div class="slide__inner stagger-children">
      <h2 class="slide__heading">Deliverables</h2>
      <ul class="deliverables-list">
        <li>
          <span class="deliverable__name">Portfolio Set</span>
          <span class="deliverable__desc">12&ndash;20 hero images across the three-act structure</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="deliverable__name">Editorial Series</span>
          <span class="deliverable__desc">3&ndash;4 Substack posts: concept &amp; BTS, photo essay, location deep dive</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="deliverable__name">Commercial Pitch</span>
          <span class="deliverable__desc">Tailored brand decks for aviation, coffee, and lifestyle partners</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="deliverable__name">Social Content</span>
          <span class="deliverable__desc">BTS during production, full reveal after edit, parallel edit reel</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="slide__text">Full edit pass within 2 weeks of each shoot.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 13. Partnership Fit ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-13">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Partnership Fit</h2>
      <p class="slide__text reveal">
        The concept is modular&mdash;each location can highlight a different partner.
      </p>
      <div class="partnership-grid stagger-children">
        <div class="partner">
          <div class="partner__name">Pilatus</div>
          <p class="partner__angle">Aircraft as hero. Swiss homecoming story. Brand heritage at altitude.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="partner">
          <div class="partner__name">La Marzocco / Mazzer</div>
          <p class="partner__angle">Equipment performing in extreme conditions. Precision under duress.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="partner">
          <div class="partner__name">Specialty Coffee Brand</div>
          <p class="partner__angle">Origin story meets altitude. Extraction at 10,000 feet.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="partner">
          <div class="partner__name">Cycling / Outdoor Brand</div>
          <p class="partner__angle">Athletes as guests. Gear in context. Earned arrival.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="slide__text fade-in" style="text-align: center; margin-inline: auto;">
        One concept. Many runways. Tailored to each partner.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 14. Contact ======= -->
  <section class="slide slide--contact" id="slide-14">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <h2 class="slide__heading slide__heading--large reveal">Let's find the next runway.</h2>
      <div class="contact-info fade-in">
        <p><strong>Corbin Heist</strong></p>
        <p>Heist Studio</p>
        <p><a href="https://heist.studio">heist.studio</a></p>
        <p><a href="mailto:corbin@heist.studio">corbin@heist.studio</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</PitchLayout>
